This git repository contains examples that are used in the laboratory
exercise for the VSD lectures and labs on physical verification (2021).

Lab 3, Design Rule Checking (DRC)

Contents:
----------------------
Exercise 1:  Width, Spacing, Wide spacing, and Notch rules
Exercise 2:  Minimum area and minimum hole rules
Exercise 3:  Vias and via rules
Exercise 4:  Wells and taps
Exercise 5:  Derived layer rules
Exercise 6:  Devices and device rules
Exercise 7:  Off-grid rules, angle rules, overlap rules 
Exercise 8:  Unimplemented rules:  Seal ring and SRAM
Exercise 9:  Latchup rules
Exercise 10: Antenna rules
Exercise 11: Density rules
Exercise 12: Do it yourself!
